Prep DEM

Feature preserving smooth Fill single cell pits Breach larger depressions

#dem <- raster("hydem1m.tif/hydem1m.tif")

wbt_feature_preserving_smoothing(
  dem = "hydem1m.tif/hydem1m.tif",
  output = "hydem1m_smooth.tif",
  filter = 5,
  norm_diff = 15,
  num_iter = 3,
  max_diff = 0.5)

wbt_fill_single_cell_pits(
  dem = "hydem1m_smooth.tif",
  output = "hydem1m_smooth_filled.tif")

wbt_breach_depressions_least_cost(
  dem = "hydem1m_smooth_filled.tif",
  output = "hydem1m_smooth_filled_breached.tif",
  dist = 5,
  fill = TRUE)

wbt_hillshade(
  dem = "hydem1m_smooth_filled_breached.tif",
  output = "hydem1m_prepped_hillshade.tif")

Look at hillshade of prepped DEM

hillshade <- raster("hydem1m_prepped_hillshade.tif")

tmap_mode("view")
tm_shape(hillshade)+
  tm_raster(style = "cont",palette = "-Greys", legend.show = FALSE)+
  tm_scale_bar()

Original topo metrics TPI 100 TWId EDb Uaab New metrics moving forward in Whitebox or RSAGA Max slope (1m) TPI 20, 100, 500 (SAGA, 5m) Multi-resolution valley bottom (MRVB; SAGA; 5m) TWId (GRASS, raster calculator; 5m) Feature preserving filter DEM (GRASS) Ln(UAA)/tan(downslope index 5m distance) SAGA
